subSubSection.paragraph:
[New Japanese name: Shirakawa-yadokari] (
Figs. 1–5
)

Pleon (
Fig. 5
) dextrally twisted. Female with 4 unpaired pleopods; second to fourth pleopods slightly unequally biramous, fifth much smaller than preceding pleopods, uniramous. Uropods markedly asymmetrical, left about twice of right in length; protopods unarmed.
